This paper deals with privacy-preserving statistical hypothesis testing, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of local differential privacy (LDP) is a key aspect of the proposed approach, which is a technique commonly used in privacy-preserving data analysis (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of real-world datasets, which suggests a potential connection to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
